==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aye-aye
<hw>Aye"-aye`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native
name, prob. from its cry.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A singular
nocturnal quadruped, allied to the lemurs, found in Madagascar
(<spn>Cheiromys Madagascariensis</spn>), remarkable for its long
fingers, sharp nails, and rodent-like incisor teeth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ayegreen</ent>⟦br⟧
